Let's apply the formal definition to the student-course example.

• **Set X (Students):** {Nimal, Sarath, Wijay, Fathima}
• **Set Y (Courses):** {Economics, Marketing Management, Financial Mathematics}

The relation R, representing the enrollments shown in the table, can be written as a set of ordered pairs:

<mark-critical>R = {(Nimal, Economics), (Wijay, Marketing Management), (Sarath, Marketing Management), (Fathima, Economics), (Wijay, Financial Math), (Sarath, Economics)}</mark-critical>

Since the pair (Nimal, Economics) is in the set R, we can write **Nimal R Economics**.
